# Documentation Sync Rules

Update the correct Obsidian note whenever one of the following triggers occurs. Do not wait to be asked.

## Trigger → file mapping

| Trigger | File to update |
|---|---|
| Feature or task completed | `obsidian/02-dev-logs/YYYY-MM-DD.md` — append what was done and the outcome |
| New architectural pattern or structural decision made | `obsidian/03-decisions/` — create a new ADR using `_template.md` |
| Architecture or component changed | `obsidian/00-project/architecture.md` |
| New tool, library, or language added | `obsidian/00-project/tech-stack.md` |
| Project scope, goal, or feature set changed | `obsidian/00-project/project-brief.md` |
| New task identified or milestone adjusted | `obsidian/01-planning/backlog.md` or `obsidian/01-planning/roadmap.md` |

## Hard rules

- Never end a working session without appending an entry to today's dev log (`obsidian/02-dev-logs/YYYY-MM-DD.md`). Create the file if it does not exist, using `obsidian/02-dev-logs/_template.md` as the base.
- If a decision was made during the session and no ADR exists for it, create one in `obsidian/03-decisions/` before closing.
- Dev log file names must always follow the `YYYY-MM-DD.md` format.
